This patch works around a bug in Automake, where the C linker mechanism
is used instead of the C++ linker mechanism.

The weird thing is that this only happens for the particular Makefile.in
in the examples/components/ directory -- so it probably has something to
do with either the particular succession of settings in th
examples/components/Makefile.am (which deviates a little from the other
examples/*/Makefile.am files), or with the conditional compile/link
settings. 20000513 mortene.

